.TH LIBYAJL 3 "2026-05-06" "yajl 2.1.0" "InterGenOS Library Manual"
.SH NAME
libyajl \- Yet Another JSON Library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <yajl/yajl_parse.h>
.br
.B #include <yajl/yajl_gen.h>
.br
.B #include <yajl/yajl_tree.h>
.PP
.B cc
[\fIflags\fR] \fIfile\fR \fB-lyajl\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fByajl\fP is a small, fast, event-driven (SAX-style) and tree-based
(DOM-style) JSON parser and generator written in ANSI C.
.PP
The library provides:
.TP
.B yajl_parse.h
Streaming JSON parser with callbacks for map/array start/end, keys,
strings, numbers, booleans, and null values.
.TP
.B yajl_gen.h
Programmatic JSON generator that produces properly-formatted output.
.TP
.B yajl_tree.h
Document-object-model parser that reads entire JSON input into an
in-memory tree suitable for random access.
.PP
Two command-line utilities are also provided:
\fBjson_reformat\fP pretty-prints JSON input, and \fBjson_verify\fP
validates JSON syntax.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR json_reformat (1),
.BR json_verify (1)
.PP
Project homepage:
.UR https://github.com/lloyd/yajl
.UE .
